# toggle_defaults.golden — P3.3a default-off discipline gate
#
# Source of truth for the DEFAULT POLARITY of every catalog SRENIX_* toggle that
# gates a probe / analyzer / fixer / investigator REGISTRATION. Format:
#
#   SRENIX_TOGGLE_NAME on|off
#
#   on  = trigger is REGISTERED unless the operator opts out (`!= "off"`).
#         i.e. ships DEFAULT-ON.
#   off = trigger is registered only when explicitly enabled (`== "true"`).
#         i.e. ships DEFAULT-OFF.
#
# DISCIPLINE (the roadmap done-criteria that were abandoned, causing the
# v1.23.0 M5/M6 unwired-but-default-on regression): a NET-NEW probe/analyzer
# toggle should ship DEFAULT-OFF, soak 7 days, then flip to default-on in the
# next release. The accompanying default_off_test.go FAILS when a toggle is
# added or a polarity flips, forcing the developer to (1) confirm the new
# toggle ships default-OFF unless a soak rationale is recorded, and
# (2) consciously update this golden.
#
# GRANDFATHERING: every entry below reflects the CURRENT (pre-discipline)
# state. The many `on` entries here PREDATE this gate and are grandfathered —
# the gate only catches NET-NEW additions or polarity FLIPS, not the existing
# default-on inventory.
# SOAK RATIONALE (base-probe + core-analyzer toggles, 2026-06): the six base
# probes (Ceph/Nodes/Postgres/PVCs/CriticalWorkloads/Endpoints) and seven core
# analyzers (secret-chain/cert/image-auth) below are NOT net-new triggers —
# they have been registered UNCONDITIONALLY since v1.0 and have years of
# production soak. The toggles only add the documented opt-out
# (SRENIX_PROBE_<NAME>=off / SRENIX_ANALYZER_<NAME>=off); shipping them default-OFF
# would be a behavior REGRESSION, silently disabling the product's core
# signal. Default-ON preserves the status quo exactly.
SRENIX_ANALYZER_CAPACITY_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_CERT_EXPIRY on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_FAILED_PODS on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_FAILING_EXTERNAL_SECRETS on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_IMAGE_PULL_AUTH on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_PROACTIVE_SECRET_KEY_CHECK on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_SECRET_KEY_MISSING on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_TLS_SECRET_MISMATCH on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_UNPROVISIONED_SECRET on
SRENIX_PROBE_CEPH on
SRENIX_PROBE_CRITICAL_WORKLOADS on
SRENIX_PROBE_ENDPOINTS on
SRENIX_PROBE_NODES on
SRENIX_PROBE_POSTGRES on
SRENIX_PROBE_PVCS on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_CONFIG_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_CRONJOB_STUCK on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_DISRUPTION_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_DNS_CHAIN_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_GITOPS_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_LOG_PATTERN_MATCHER on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_NETPOL_PROPOSER on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_OOMKILL_RECURRENCE on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_PV_ORPHAN on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_RBAC_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_SECURITY_DRIFT on
SRENIX_ANALYZER_WORKLOAD_STATE_DRIFT on
SRENIX_FIXER_TLS_SECRET_MISMATCH off
SRENIX_INVESTIGATOR on
SRENIX_PROBE_ARGOCD_APP on
SRENIX_PROBE_CRASHLOOP on
SRENIX_PROBE_DAEMONSETS on
SRENIX_PROBE_ETCD on
SRENIX_PROBE_FAILED_MOUNTS on
SRENIX_PROBE_GPU_NODES on
SRENIX_PROBE_HPA_SCALING on
SRENIX_PROBE_K3S_DATASTORE on
SRENIX_PROBE_K3S_LOCALPATH on
SRENIX_PROBE_KONG on
SRENIX_PROBE_KONG_ROUTES on
SRENIX_PROBE_NODE_PRESSURE on
SRENIX_PROBE_PENDING_PODS on
SRENIX_PROBE_TRAEFIK_ROUTES on
SRENIX_PROBE_VELERO on
# SOAK RATIONALE (per-cloud-probe toggles, 2026-06 / O6): the 30 cloud probes
# are NOT net-new triggers — they have been registered UNCONDITIONALLY (gated
# only by the per-provider enabled switch) since v1.8. The SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_*
# toggles only add the documented opt-out promised by the chart's
# cloud.<provider>.probes.* values, which previously were decorative.
# Default-ON preserves the status quo exactly; default-OFF would silently
# disable every cloud signal on upgrade. EKS/GKE/AKS each gate BOTH the
# control-plane and node-pool probes (one values key per asset).
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_RDS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_EBS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_EKS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_IAM on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_ALB on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_ACM on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_KMS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_S3 on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AWS_VPC on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_CLOUDSQL on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_DISKS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_GKE on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_IAM on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_SUBNETS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_LB on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_CERTS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_GCS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_GCP_KMS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_SQL on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_DISKS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_AKS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_IDENTITIES on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_SUBNETS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_APPGW on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_CERTS on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_STORAGE on
SRENIX_CLOUD_PROBE_AZURE_KEYVAULTS on
